I've been converting several GLSL shaders to Godot and hit a few strange errors that change if I move code around.  Here is one I was able to replicate in a concise example.  If the foobar function simply exists in the file it causes the unrelated test function to cause a compile error.  Also just swapping the order of foobar and test makes it work ok.   Very difficult to debug and trace these errors down but I'll try to submit other examples as I can.  I can send a zip of this test case as a project by email if desired.

I'm using 1.1 Stable under windows 7 64 bit.

```
// Uncomment the following and the shader fails to compile with error:
// "error(1,0): Invalid initializer for variable: testR"
// Also if test is defined before foobar it *will* work ok
/*
float foobar(vec2 co){
    return 1.0;
}
*/

vec2 test(vec2 p)
{
    return p;
}

vec2 testR = test(UV);
COLOR = color(testR, 0.0, 1.0);
```

